main event: A single tall and narrow vertical structure was seen emerging from a cloudy background in Emmons, Minnesota in 1959.
interesting points: The structure was the only visible object in the photograph, with no other objects or human subjects present.
The report is sourced from Lt. Richard J. Emmons, USAF.
The photograph shows a potentially unexplained vertical structure in the sky.
The location of the sighting is Emmons, Minnesota.
sighted object: a single tall and narrow vertical structure
